<h1 class="headerLeft">DoD Unique Coding Considerations</h1>
<p>There are several unique coding considerations that coders and billers face when coding or billing medical encounters in the DoD environment.  
While many of these issues are unheard of in the civilian community, they are important to the collection of biostatistical data in the investigation of population health issues for DoD.</p>
<p>  
<h1 class="headerLeft">&nbsp;</h1>
<p>Others may in turn be caused by systems contraints due to the advancing technology and sophisticated integration of a number of medical information systems. </p>
 
<h1 class="headerLeft">&nbsp;</h1>
<p>Occasionally, despite that advancement, some "work arounds" are required to allow us to proceed in our coding while a system change request (SCR) is in development.</p> 
<p>  
<h1 class="headerLeft">&nbsp;</h1>
<p>Please understand, the AMEDD position is coding accurately to the official guidelines (ICD10-CM, CPT/HCPCS, Coding Clinic, CPT Assistant, and many NCCI and CMS edits).</p>


